.TH "build_set_exc_base" 9 "build_set_exc_base" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
build_set_exc_base \- Assemble code to write exception base address.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" build_set_exc_base
.BI "(u32 **p "  ","
.BI "unsigned int reg "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "p" 12
Code buffer pointer.
.IP "reg" 12
Source register (generated code may set WG bit in \fIreg\fP).
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Assemble code to modify the exception base address in the EBase register,
using the appropriately sized access and setting the WG bit if necessary.
